{
  "video_id": "-I3e6Mkfp7M",
  "title": "My $500 house in Detroit -- and the neighbors who helped me rebuild it | Drew Philp",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12743.0,
      "end_time": 17120.0,
      "text": "In 2009, I bought a house in Detroit for 500 dollars."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17891.0,
      "end_time": 21651.0,
      "text": "It had no windows, no plumbing, no electricity"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21676.0,
      "end_time": 23116.0,
      "text": "and it was filled with trash."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24344.0,
      "end_time": 28297.0,
      "text": "The first floor held nearly 10,000 pounds of garbage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 28321.0,
      "end_time": 31164.0,
      "text": "and that included the better part of a Dodge Caravan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31188.0,
      "end_time": 33466.0,
      "text": "cut into chunks with a reciprocating saw."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 33490.0,
      "end_time": 34685.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34709.0,
      "end_time": 36879.0,
      "text": "I lived nearly two years without heat,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36903.0,
      "end_time": 40387.0,
      "text": "woke up out of a dead sleep multiple times to gunshots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 40411.0,
      "end_time": 44447.0,
      "text": "was attacked by a pack of wild dogs"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 44471.0,
      "end_time": 48147.0,
      "text": "and ripped my kitchen cabinets from an abandoned school"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 48171.0,
      "end_time": 51950.0,
      "text": "as they were actively tearing that school down."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 52626.0,
      "end_time": 55683.0,
      "text": "This, of course, is the Detroit that your hear about."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 55707.0,
      "end_time": 57316.0,
      "text": "Make no mistake, it&#39;s real."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 58929.0,
      "end_time": 60737.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s another Detroit, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 60761.0,
      "end_time": 62829.0,
      "text": "Another Detroit that&#39;s more hopeful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 62853.0,
      "end_time": 64144.0,
      "text": "more innovative,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 64168.00000000001,
      "end_time": 66319.0,
      "text": "and may just provide some of the answers"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 66343.0,
      "end_time": 69292.0,
      "text": "to cities struggling to reinvent themselves everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 70450.0,
      "end_time": 74877.0,
      "text": "These answers, however, do not necessarily adhere to conventional wisdom"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 74901.0,
      "end_time": 76304.0,
      "text": "about good development."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 77472.0,
      "end_time": 81708.0,
      "text": "I think Detroit&#39;s real strength boils down to two words:"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 81732.0,
      "end_time": 83850.0,
      "text": "radical neighborliness."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 84529.0,
      "end_time": 87286.0,
      "text": "And I wasn&#39;t able to see it myself until I lived there."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 88684.0,
      "end_time": 89835.0,
      "text": "About a decade ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 89859.0,
      "end_time": 93381.0,
      "text": "I moved to Detroit with no friends, no job and no money,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 93406.0,
      "end_time": 96597.0,
      "text": "at a time when it seemed like everyone else was moving out."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 96621.0,
      "end_time": 99351.0,
      "text": "Between 2000 and 2010,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 99376.0,
      "end_time": 102870.0,
      "text": "25 percent of the city&#39;s population left."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 102111.0,
      "end_time": 105128.0,
      "text": "This included about half of the elementary-aged children."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 106128.0,
      "end_time": 108342.0,
      "text": "This was after six decades of decline."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 108718.0,
      "end_time": 113105.0,
      "text": "A city built for almost two million was down to less than 800,000."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 114212.0,
      "end_time": 117704.0,
      "text": "What you usually don&#39;t hear is that people didn&#39;t go very far."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 118826.0,
      "end_time": 122125.0,
      "text": "The population of the Detroit metro area itself"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 122149.0,
      "end_time": 124574.0,
      "text": "has largely remained steady since the &#39;70s."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 125470.0,
      "end_time": 127993.0,
      "text": "Most people who left Detroit just went to the suburbs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 128169.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131648.0,
      "text": "while the 139 square miles of the city deteriorated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 132804.0,
      "end_time": 137954.0,
      "text": "leaving some estimates as high as 40 square miles of abandoned land --"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 137978.0,
      "end_time": 139875.0,
      "text": "about the size of San Francisco."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 141770.0,
      "end_time": 145938.0,
      "text": "Aside from platitudes such as the vague and agentless \"deindustrialization,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 145962.0,
      "end_time": 148858.0,
      "text": "Detroit&#39;s exodus can be summed up with two structures:"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 148883.0,
      "end_time": 150730.0,
      "text": "freeways and walls."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 151612.0,
      "end_time": 152814.0,
      "text": "The freeways,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 152838.0,
      "end_time": 155394.0,
      "text": "coupled with massive governmental subsidies"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 155419.0,
      "end_time": 159370.0,
      "text": "for the suburbs via infrastructure and home loans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 159610.0,
      "end_time": 161653.0,
      "text": "allowed people to leave the city at will,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 161677.0,
      "end_time": 165392.0,
      "text": "taking with it tax base, jobs and education dollars."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 166222.0,
      "end_time": 169143.0,
      "text": "The walls made sure only certain people could leave."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 170111.0,
      "end_time": 171261.0,
      "text": "In multiple places,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 171285.0,
      "end_time": 174984.0,
      "text": "brick and concrete walls separate city and suburbs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 175800.0,
      "end_time": 176515.0,
      "text": "white and black,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 176539.0,
      "end_time": 178935.0,
      "text": "running directly across municipal streets"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 178960.0,
      "end_time": 180594.0,
      "text": "and through neighborhoods."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 180618.0,
      "end_time": 184635.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re mere physical manifestations of racist housing practices"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 184659.0,
      "end_time": 185817.0,
      "text": "such as redlining,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 185842.0,
      "end_time": 187619.0,
      "text": "[Denying services to people of color]"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 187643.0,
      "end_time": 188793.0,
      "text": "restrictive covenants"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 189972.0,
      "end_time": 191318.0,
      "text": "and outright terror."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 191764.0,
      "end_time": 195868.0,
      "text": "In 1971, the Ku Klux Klan bombed 10 school buses"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 195892.0,
      "end_time": 198741.0,
      "text": "rather than have them transport integrated students."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 199772.0,
      "end_time": 203828.0,
      "text": "All these have made Detroit the most racially segregated metro area"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 203852.0,
      "end_time": 205229.0,
      "text": "in the United States."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 206735.0,
      "end_time": 208677.0,
      "text": "I grew up in a small town in Michigan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 208701.0,
      "end_time": 210811.0,
      "text": "the son of a relatively blue-collar family."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 211294.0,
      "end_time": 213817.0,
      "text": "And after university, I wanted to do something --"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 213841.0,
      "end_time": 214992.0,
      "text": "probably na√Øvely --"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 215160.0,
      "end_time": 216166.0,
      "text": "to help."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 216594.0,
      "end_time": 220310.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t want to be one of the almost 50 percent of college graduates"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 220550.0,
      "end_time": 221986.0,
      "text": "leaving the state at the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 222100.0,
      "end_time": 225429.0,
      "text": "and I thought I might use my fancy college education at home"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 225453.0,
      "end_time": 226860.0,
      "text": "for something positive."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 227741.0,
      "end_time": 231576.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d been reading this great American philosopher named Grace Lee Boggs"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 231600.0,
      "end_time": 233355.0,
      "text": "who happened to live in Detroit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 233379.0,
      "end_time": 236109.0,
      "text": "and she said something I can&#39;t forget."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 236847.0,
      "end_time": 240728.0,
      "text": "\"The most radical thing that I ever did was to stay put.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 242355.0,
      "end_time": 246260.0,
      "text": "I thought buying a house might indelibly tie me to the city"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 246284.0,
      "end_time": 249417.0,
      "text": "while acting as a physical protest to these walls and freeways."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 250840.0,
      "end_time": 252656.0,
      "text": "Because grants and loans weren&#39;t available to everyone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 252680.0,
      "end_time": 254990.0,
      "text": "I decided I was going to do this without them"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 255140.0,
      "end_time": 256897.0,
      "text": "and that I would wage my personal fight"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 256921.0,
      "end_time": 260337.0,
      "text": "against the city that had loomed over my childhood with power tools."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 261284.0,
      "end_time": 264849.0,
      "text": "I eventually found an abandoned house in a neighborhood called Poletown."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 265730.0,
      "end_time": 267834.0,
      "text": "It looked like the apocalypse had descended."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 268585.0,
      "end_time": 270268.0,
      "text": "The neighborhood was prairie land."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 270292.0,
      "end_time": 273530.0,
      "text": "A huge, open expanse of waist-high grass"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 273770.0,
      "end_time": 276848.0,
      "text": "cluttered only by a handful of crippled, abandoned structures"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 276872.0,
      "end_time": 279220.0,
      "text": "and a few brave holdouts with well-kept homes."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 280960.0,
      "end_time": 285870.0,
      "text": "Just a 15-minute bike ride from the baseball stadium downtown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 285111.0,
      "end_time": 287647.0,
      "text": "the neighborhood was positively rural."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 288921.0,
      "end_time": 292484.0,
      "text": "What houses were left looked like cardboard boxes left in the rain;"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 292508.0,
      "end_time": 295501.0,
      "text": "two-story monstrosities with wide-open shells"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 295525.0,
      "end_time": 296897.0,
      "text": "and melted porches."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 297348.0,
      "end_time": 300915.0,
      "text": "One of the most striking things I remember were the rosebushes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 300939.0,
      "end_time": 304166.0,
      "text": "forgotten and running wild over tumbled-down fences,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 304190.0,
      "end_time": 306119.0,
      "text": "no longer cared for by anyone."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 307565.0,
      "end_time": 310499.0,
      "text": "This was my house on the day I boarded it up"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 310523.0,
      "end_time": 312887.0,
      "text": "to protect it from the elements and further decay."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 313344.0,
      "end_time": 316617.0,
      "text": "I eventually purchased it from the county in a live auction."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 316641.0,
      "end_time": 318452.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d assumed the neighborhood was dead."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 318476.0,
      "end_time": 321201.0,
      "text": "That I was some kind of pioneer."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 322223.0,
      "end_time": 324110.0,
      "text": "Well, I couldn&#39;t have been more wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 324554.0,
      "end_time": 326490.0,
      "text": "I was in no way a pioneer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 326740.0,
      "end_time": 328541.0,
      "text": "and would come to understand how offensive that is."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 329844.0,
      "end_time": 333582.0,
      "text": "One of the first things I learned was to add my voice to the chorus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 333606.0,
      "end_time": 335581.0,
      "text": "not overwrite what was already happening."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 336127.0,
      "end_time": 338699.0,
      "text": "(Voice breaking) Because the neighborhood hadn&#39;t died."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 338723.0,
      "end_time": 341503.0,
      "text": "It had just transformed in a way that was difficult to see"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 341527.0,
      "end_time": 342844.0,
      "text": "if you didn&#39;t live there."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 343274.0,
      "end_time": 345820.0,
      "text": "Poletown was home to an incredibly resourceful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 345844.0,
      "end_time": 349539.0,
      "text": "incredibly intelligent and incredibly resilient community."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 350499.0,
      "end_time": 355200.0,
      "text": "It was there I first experienced the power of radical neighborliness."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 355985.0,
      "end_time": 358509.0,
      "text": "During the year I worked on my house before moving in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 358533.0,
      "end_time": 361100.0,
      "text": "I lived in a microcommunity inside Poletown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 361250.0,
      "end_time": 364741.0,
      "text": "founded by a wild and virtuous farmer named Paul Weertz."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 365522.0,
      "end_time": 368320.0,
      "text": "Paul was a teacher in a Detroit public school"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 368560.0,
      "end_time": 369835.0,
      "text": "for pregnant and parenting mothers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 369859.0,
      "end_time": 372928.0,
      "text": "and his idea was to teach the young women to raise their children"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 372952.0,
      "end_time": 374675.0,
      "text": "by first raising plants and animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 375785.0,
      "end_time": 380510.0,
      "text": "While the national average graduation rate for pregnant teens is about 40 percent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 380750.0,
      "end_time": 383260.0,
      "text": "at Catherine Ferguson Academy it was often above 90,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 383284.0,
      "end_time": 385810.0,
      "text": "in part due to Paul&#39;s ingenuity."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 385716.0,
      "end_time": 388710.0,
      "text": "Paul brought much of this innovation to his block in Poletown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 388734.0,
      "end_time": 391292.0,
      "text": "which he&#39;d stewarded for more than 30 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 391316.0,
      "end_time": 393804.0,
      "text": "purchasing houses when they were abandoned,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 393828.0,
      "end_time": 396924.0,
      "text": "convincing his friends to move in and neighbors to stay"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 396949.0,
      "end_time": 400202.0,
      "text": "and helping those who wanted to buy their own and fix them up."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 400886.0,
      "end_time": 404783.0,
      "text": "In a neighborhood where many blocks now only hold one or two houses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 404807.0,
      "end_time": 407350.0,
      "text": "all the homes on Paul&#39;s block stand."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 407590.0,
      "end_time": 409631.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s an incredible testament to the power of community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 409655.0,
      "end_time": 410974.0,
      "text": "to staying in one place"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 410998.0,
      "end_time": 413686.0,
      "text": "and to taking ownership of one&#39;s own surroundings --"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 413710.0,
      "end_time": 415626.0,
      "text": "of simply doing it yourself."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 416244.0,
      "end_time": 420185.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the kind of place where black doctors live next to white hipsters"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 420209.0,
      "end_time": 422200.0,
      "text": "next to immigrant mothers from Hungary"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 422440.0,
      "end_time": 424837.0,
      "text": "or talented writers from the jungles of Belize,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 424861.0,
      "end_time": 427960.0,
      "text": "showing me Detroit wasn&#39;t just black and white,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 427120.0,
      "end_time": 429842.0,
      "text": "and diversity could flourish when it&#39;s encouraged."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 430466.0,
      "end_time": 434762.0,
      "text": "Each year, neighbors assemble to bale hay for the farm animals on the block,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 434786.0,
      "end_time": 437992.0,
      "text": "teaching me just how much a small group of people can get done"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 438160.0,
      "end_time": 439707.0,
      "text": "when they work together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 439731.0,
      "end_time": 444133.0,
      "text": "and the magnetism of fantastical yet practical ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 444929.0,
      "end_time": 449321.0,
      "text": "Radical neighborliness is every house behind Paul&#39;s block burning down,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 449346.0,
      "end_time": 452578.0,
      "text": "and instead of letting it fill up with trash and despair,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 452602.0,
      "end_time": 455929.0,
      "text": "Paul and the surrounding community creating a giant circular garden"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 455953.0,
      "end_time": 459607.0,
      "text": "ringed with dozens of fruit trees, beehives and garden plots"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 459631.0,
      "end_time": 461433.0,
      "text": "for anyone that wants one,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 461457.0,
      "end_time": 464536.0,
      "text": "helping me see that our challenges can often be assets."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 465440.0,
      "end_time": 469370.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s where residents are experimenting with renewable energy and urban farming"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 469394.0,
      "end_time": 472267.0,
      "text": "and offering their skills and discoveries to others,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 472291.0,
      "end_time": 475149.0,
      "text": "illustrating we don&#39;t necessarily have to beg the government"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 475173.0,
      "end_time": 476426.0,
      "text": "to provide solutions."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 476450.0,
      "end_time": 477806.0,
      "text": "We can start ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 478344.0,
      "end_time": 479562.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s where, for months,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 479586.0,
      "end_time": 481999.0,
      "text": "one of my neighbors left her front door unlocked"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 482230.0,
      "end_time": 484791.0,
      "text": "in one of the most violent and dangerous cities in America"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 484815.0,
      "end_time": 487817.0,
      "text": "so I could have a shower whenever I needed to go to work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 487841.0,
      "end_time": 489305.0,
      "text": "as I didn&#39;t yet have one."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 490416.0,
      "end_time": 493131.0,
      "text": "It was when it came time to raise the beam on my own house"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 493155.0,
      "end_time": 494750.0,
      "text": "that holds the structure aloft --"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 494774.0,
      "end_time": 498177.0,
      "text": "a beam that I cut out of an abandoned recycling factory down the street"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 498201.0,
      "end_time": 500459.0,
      "text": "when not a single wall was left standing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 500483.0,
      "end_time": 503788.0,
      "text": "a dozen residents of Poletown showed up to help lift it, Amish style."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 505970.0,
      "end_time": 509143.0,
      "text": "Radical neighborliness is a zygote that grows into a worldview"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 509167.0,
      "end_time": 513395.0,
      "text": "that ends up in homes and communities rebuilt in ways that respect humanity"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 513419.0,
      "end_time": 514771.0,
      "text": "and the environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 514796.00000000006,
      "end_time": 518143.00000000006,
      "text": "It&#39;s realizing we have the power to create the world anew together"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 518167.00000000006,
      "end_time": 520877.00000000006,
      "text": "and to do it ourselves when our governments refuse."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 522150.0,
      "end_time": 524405.0,
      "text": "This is the Detroit that you don&#39;t hear much about."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 525271.0,
      "end_time": 528564.0,
      "text": "The Detroit between the ruin porn on one hand"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 528589.0,
      "end_time": 530332.0,
      "text": "and the hipster coffee shops"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 530356.0,
      "end_time": 532946.0,
      "text": "and billionaires saving the city on the other."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 533520.0,
      "end_time": 535175.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a third way to rebuild,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 535199.0,
      "end_time": 538210.0,
      "text": "and it declines to make the same mistakes of the past."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 539285.0,
      "end_time": 540435.0,
      "text": "While building my house,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 540460.0,
      "end_time": 542893.0,
      "text": "I found something I didn&#39;t know I was looking for --"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 542917.0,
      "end_time": 544122.0,
      "text": "what a lot of millennials"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 544146.0,
      "end_time": 546857.0,
      "text": "and people who are moving back to cities are looking for."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 547195.0,
      "end_time": 550979.0,
      "text": "Radical neighborliness is just another word for true community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 551300.0,
      "end_time": 553140.0,
      "text": "the kind bound my memory and history,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 553164.0,
      "end_time": 557512.0,
      "text": "mutual trust and familiarity built over years and irreplaceable."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 558280.0,
      "end_time": 560254.0,
      "text": "And now, as you may have heard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 560278.0,
      "end_time": 562454.0,
      "text": "Detroit is having a renaissance"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 562478.0,
      "end_time": 565262.0,
      "text": "and pulling itself up from the ashes of despair,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 565287.0,
      "end_time": 568905.0,
      "text": "and the children and grandchildren of those who fled are returning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 568929.0,
      "end_time": 570790.0,
      "text": "which is true."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 571198.0,
      "end_time": 574738.0,
      "text": "What isn&#39;t true is that this renaissance is reaching most Detroiters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 574762.0,
      "end_time": 576781.0,
      "text": "or even more than a small fraction of them"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 576806.0,
      "end_time": 579193.0,
      "text": "that don&#39;t live in the central areas of the city."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 579869.0,
      "end_time": 583155.0,
      "text": "These are the kind of people that have been in Detroit for generations"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 583179.0,
      "end_time": 584468.0,
      "text": "and are mostly black."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 584891.0,
      "end_time": 586363.0,
      "text": "In 2016 alone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 586387.0,
      "end_time": 587536.0,
      "text": "just last year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 588965.0,
      "end_time": 591380.0,
      "text": "(Voice breaking) one in six houses in Detroit"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 591404.0,
      "end_time": 592714.0,
      "text": "had their water shut off."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 595570.0,
      "end_time": 596207.0,
      "text": "Excuse me."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 598622.0,
      "end_time": 602930.0,
      "text": "The United Nations has called this a violation of human rights."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 603134.0,
      "end_time": 606542.0,
      "text": "And since 2005, one in three houses --"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 606566.0,
      "end_time": 608200.0,
      "text": "think about this, please --"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 609824.0,
      "end_time": 613389.0,
      "text": "one in every three houses has been foreclosed in the city,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 613413.0,
      "end_time": 616969.0,
      "text": "representing a population about the size of Buffalo, New York."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 617649.0,
      "end_time": 618799.0,
      "text": "(Sniffles)"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 619513.0,
      "end_time": 624423.0,
      "text": "One in three houses foreclosed is not a crisis of personal responsibility;"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 624447.0,
      "end_time": 625597.0,
      "text": "it is systemic."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 626640.0,
      "end_time": 629340.0,
      "text": "Many Detroiters, myself included,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 629364.0,
      "end_time": 633530.0,
      "text": "are worried segregation is now returning to the city itself"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 633770.0,
      "end_time": 635490.0,
      "text": "on the coattails of this renaissance."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 638142.0,
      "end_time": 639340.0,
      "text": "Ten years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 639364.0,
      "end_time": 641651.0,
      "text": "it was not possible to go anywhere in Detroit"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 641675.0,
      "end_time": 645281.0,
      "text": "and be in a crowd completely made of white people."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 645305.0,
      "end_time": 648204.0,
      "text": "Now, troublingly, that is possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 648940.0,
      "end_time": 654766.0,
      "text": "This is the price that we&#39;re paying for conventional economic resurgence."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 654790.0,
      "end_time": 658501.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re creating two Detroits, two classes of citizens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 658525.0,
      "end_time": 660286.0,
      "text": "cracking the community apart."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 660725.0,
      "end_time": 662373.0,
      "text": "For all the money and subsidies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 662397.0,
      "end_time": 664640.0,
      "text": "for all the streetlights installed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 664880.0,
      "end_time": 666933.0,
      "text": "the dollars for new stadiums and slick advertisements"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 666957.0,
      "end_time": 668365.0,
      "text": "and positive buzz,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 668389.0,
      "end_time": 672852.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re shutting off water to tens of thousands of people"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 672876.0,
      "end_time": 674624.0,
      "text": "living right on the Great Lakes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 674648.0,
      "end_time": 676578.0,
      "text": "the world&#39;s largest source of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 677636.0,
      "end_time": 679839.0,
      "text": "Separate has always meant unequal."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 680896.0,
      "end_time": 683450.0,
      "text": "This is a grave mistake for all of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 684132.0,
      "end_time": 686840.0,
      "text": "When economic development comes at the cost of community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 686865.0,
      "end_time": 689520.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s not just those who have lost their homes"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 689760.0,
      "end_time": 691130.0,
      "text": "or access to water who are harmed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 691370.0,
      "end_time": 694709.0,
      "text": "but it breaks little pieces of our own humanity as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 698276.0,
      "end_time": 700192.0,
      "text": "None of us can truly be free,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 700216.0,
      "end_time": 702352.0,
      "text": "none of us can truly be comfortable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 702376.0,
      "end_time": 704108.0,
      "text": "until our neighbors are, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 704888.0,
      "end_time": 706714.0,
      "text": "For those of us coming in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 706738.0,
      "end_time": 709733.0,
      "text": "it means we must make sure we aren&#39;t inadvertently contributing"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 709757.0,
      "end_time": 711965.0,
      "text": "to the destruction of community again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 711990.0,
      "end_time": 713141.0,
      "text": "and to follow the lead"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 713165.0,
      "end_time": 716156.0,
      "text": "of those who have been working on these problems for years."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 716180.0,
      "end_time": 720181.0,
      "text": "In Detroit, that means average citizens deputizing themselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 720206.0,
      "end_time": 723883.0,
      "text": "to create water stations and deliveries for those who have lost access to it."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 724366.0,
      "end_time": 727125.0,
      "text": "Or clergy and teachers engaging in civil disobedience"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 727149.0,
      "end_time": 728896.0,
      "text": "to block water shutoff trucks."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 729420.0,
      "end_time": 733286.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s organizations buying back foreclosed homes for their inhabitants"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 733310.0,
      "end_time": 736651.0,
      "text": "or fighting misinformation on forced sales through social media"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 736676.0,
      "end_time": 738504.0,
      "text": "and volunteer-run hotlines."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 739231.0,
      "end_time": 741865.0,
      "text": "For me, it means helping others to raise the beams"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 741889.0,
      "end_time": 744107.0,
      "text": "on their own formerly abandoned houses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 744131.0,
      "end_time": 746318.0,
      "text": "or helping to educate those with privilege,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 746342.0,
      "end_time": 748326.0,
      "text": "now increasingly moving into cities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 748350.0,
      "end_time": 750479.0,
      "text": "how we might come in and support"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 750503.0,
      "end_time": 752778.0,
      "text": "rather than stress existing communities."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 752802.0,
      "end_time": 755672.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s chipping in when a small group of neighbors decides"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 755696.0,
      "end_time": 757493.0,
      "text": "to buy back a foreclosed home"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 757517.0,
      "end_time": 759671.0,
      "text": "and return the deeds to the occupants."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 760352.0,
      "end_time": 762957.0,
      "text": "And for you, for all of us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 762981.0,
      "end_time": 766910.0,
      "text": "it means finding a role to play in our own communities."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 766777.0,
      "end_time": 771308.0,
      "text": "It means living your life as a reflection of the world that you want to live in."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 771332.0,
      "end_time": 774749.0,
      "text": "It means trusting those who know the problems best --"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 774773.0,
      "end_time": 776301.0,
      "text": "the people who live them --"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 776325.0,
      "end_time": 777482.0,
      "text": "with solutions."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 778919.0,
      "end_time": 782423.0,
      "text": "I know a third way is possible because I have lived it."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 782845.0,
      "end_time": 787198.0,
      "text": "I live it right now"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 787222.0,
      "end_time": 788794.0,
      "text": "in a neighborhood called Poletown"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 788818.0,
      "end_time": 791186.0,
      "text": "in one of the most maligned cities in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 791640.0,
      "end_time": 793179.0,
      "text": "If we can do it in Detroit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 793203.0,
      "end_time": 795111.0,
      "text": "you can do it wherever you&#39;re from, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 796940.0,
      "end_time": 798600.0,
      "text": "What I&#39;ve learned over the last decade,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 798300.0,
      "end_time": 799933.0,
      "text": "building my house,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 799957.0,
      "end_time": 802944.0,
      "text": "wasn&#39;t so much about wiring or plumbing or carpentry --"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 802968.0,
      "end_time": 805622.0,
      "text": "although I did learn these things --"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 805646.0,
      "end_time": 808641.0,
      "text": "is that true change, real change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 808665.0,
      "end_time": 810472.0,
      "text": "starts first with community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 810496.0,
      "end_time": 813704.0,
      "text": "with a radical sense of what it means to be a neighbor."
